<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Evermore" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Evermore</orth> == ever; 1) at any time; but only negatively, <emph>not e.</emph> == nevermore: <cit><quote>I may not e. acknowledge thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 36.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 36, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I will not tarry, no, nor e. upon this business my appearance make in any of their courts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.131" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 131</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) at or through all times: <bibl n="shak. son 70.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 70, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.307" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 307</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 5, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.65" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 3, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.172" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 70</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.295" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 295</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.3.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 3, 101</bibl>. <cit><quote>for e.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.181" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 181</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.7.107" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 7, 107</bibl>.
<lb />3) for ever: <cit><quote>so shall I e. be bound to thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.6.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 6, 54</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>e. be blest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.68" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 68</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.414" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 414</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 2, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 123</bibl>.
<lb />Adjectively? <cit><quote>frantic-mad with e. unrest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 147.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 147, 10</bibl></cit> (Q <emph>ever-more; ever more?</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>